	"contentText": "Week 11\n  \n  \n  \n    \n\n\n\nOverview\n\n\n\n\nDiversifiable or unsystematic risk, unidversifable or systematic risk, achieving diversification through portfolios, index models, calculating the alpha and beta of an asset, Treynor-Black Model\n \n\n\n\n\nLearning Objectives\nUpon completion of this week, you will be able to understand:\n\nhow diversification helps reduce risk in a portfolio\ndecompose the risk of an asset into systematic and idiosyncratic components\nlink between systematic risk and exposure to macroeconomic variables\nthe market as the source of systematic risk in single index models\ncalculate the alpha and the beta of an asset\nuse single index models to simplify the portfolio allocation problem\nwith single index models the optimal risky portfolio becomes a combination of an active portfolio and a passive portfolio (the Treynor-Black model)\n\n \nPreparation for class\nMandatory reading: lecture 5.pdf\n    \n\nDownload lecture 5.pdf\nData: index models data.xls\n    \n\nDownload index models data.xls\nData: TreynorBlack Data New.xlsx\n    \n\nDownload TreynorBlack Data New.xlsx\nSupplement: lecture 5 supplement.pdf\n    \n\nDownload lecture 5 supplement.pdf\n\n\n\n\n \nAssignments\nInteractive brokers assignment: IB A1\nA5: TBPS\n \nClass\nClass zoom link: Class logistics\n \n \nClass Notes\nAug 28 class recording: \nhttps://cuboulder.zoom.us/rec/share/NorfanbY9jTL-px-TirE73jPOwd85_6nTCK-_9vseDz1hbBOBRN0KtL5Zl3at7Wd.3APA97wknOUmyyBJ \n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nPasscode: 13PViiZ.\nClass work: index models data work.xlsx\n    \n\nDownload index models data work.xlsx\nClass notes: Fnce3030 Nov 4.pdf\n    \n\nDownload Fnce3030 Nov 4.pdf\n \nAug 30 class recording: \nhttps://cuboulder.zoom.us/rec/share/npS-ZgU9Z8XwYrMeszlysY3VxIkP-S62TYUuc7Ltv-N6Am01xvQbkh9tB5QxL3i7.dNWKZx5wltO90aO4 \n    \n\nLinks to an external site.\nPasscode: q8!BjG#7\nClass work: TreynorBlack Data 008.xlsx\n    \n\nDownload TreynorBlack Data 008.xlsx\n\n \n  \n  \n\n",
